<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> lay something on the table <i>(UK)</i> • lay something on the table <i>(U.S.)</i></xh5><p> <i>lay something on the table (UK)—</i>raise an issue for consideration (as a parliamentary procedure): A few days later Shrewsbury <u>laid on the table</u> of the Lords a bill for limiting the duration of Parliaments.</p><p><i>lay something on the table (U.S.)—</i>suspend an issue from consideration; postpone the vote on an issue until another time: It was her proposal to <u>lay the bill on the table</u> while we undertook further research.</p> </entry>
